 or the industrial military complex

149
00:05:50,460 --> 00:05:51,520
 and a lack of gun control.

150
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:53,180
 You might see that people would say,

151
00:05:53,180 --> 00:05:55,220
 it's political outrage.

152
00:05:55,220 --> 00:05:57,260
 It's poor policy making.

153
00:05:57,260 --> 00:05:59,740
 It's people divided over issues

154
00:05:59,740 --> 00:06:03,220
 that ultimately do not matter at the cost of one another.

155
00:06:03,220 --> 00:06:04,300
 You would see that it would be something

156
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:06,820
 along the lines of an ever-evolving sexual revolution.

157
00:06:06,820 --> 00:06:10,340
 It could be economic strain, rising costs of living.

158
00:06:10,340 --> 00:06:11,860
 Anybody say amen to that one?

159
00:06:11,860 --> 00:06:14,820
 And if that's not enough,

160
00:06:14,820 --> 00:06:17,060
 if the past and if the present isn't enough,

161
00:06:17,060 --> 00:06:19,300
 you could make your way over to LA.

162
00:06:19,300 --> 00:06:20,140
 You could look at Hollywood.

163
00:06:20,140 --> 00:06:21,060
 You could see what they have to say

164
00:06:21,060 --> 00:06:24,000
 because we have a thing for prequels all of a sudden,

165
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:27,020
 most of which are not very good.

166
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:31,140
 But we have this fascination to understand what's gone wrong.

167
00:06:31,140 --> 00:06:33,060
 There's a reason that we need to not just live

168
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:34,220
 with episodes four, five, and six,

