 but we got to go back to Star Wars episodes one, two,

170
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:36,860
 and three, so that way we can understand

171
00:06:36,860 --> 00:06:39,380
 why Vader's voice sounds the way it does.

172
00:06:39,380 --> 00:06:41,500
 There's a reason why the rings of power came out

173
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:45,560
 because people have questions about where Sauron came from.

174
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:46,780
 If you wanted to go even further,

175
00:06:46,780 --> 00:06:49,580
 you could look at "Wicked," one of the rare good ones.

176
00:06:49,580 --> 00:06:51,620
 And what you can see is an explanation

177
00:06:51,620 --> 00:06:55,140
 for why we have that wicked witch of the West.

178
00:06:55,140 --> 00:06:56,940
 Everyone's asking what's gone wrong.

179
00:06:56,940 --> 00:07:01,600
 You want to know what's gone wrong?

180
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:03,560
 We did.

181
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:07,380
 We went wrong.

182
00:07:07,380 --> 00:07:11,680
 That's what the Bible tells us from page three.

183
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:16,500
 In Genesis chapter three, what we find is yes,

184
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:20,100
 one of the most iconic Bible stories ever written.

185
00:07:20,100 --> 00:07:22,980
 It is a story that not only Christians,

186
00:07:22,980 --> 00:07:24,500
 but many non-Christians know,

187
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:26,220
 because the story of Adam and Eve

188
00:07:26,220 --> 00:07:28,460
 and the snake transcends time.

189
00:07:28,460 --> 00:07:31,400
 It's one that resonates deeply with people

190
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:34,460
 because it provides an explanation for that question,

191
00:07:34,460 --> 00:07:36,940
 which we can find no good answer to.

192
00:07:36,940 --> 00:07:40,420
 And yet here's the danger of this story,

193
00:07:40,420 --> 00:07:45,420
 because it is so iconic, we have a tendency to approach it

194
00:07:45,420 --> 00:07:48,280
 and bring all of our preconceptions with us.

195
00:07:48,280 --> 00:07:51,100
 We walk into it and we don't take God on his terms.

196
00:07:51,100 --> 00:07:53,100
 We take the story on someone else's terms.

197
00:07:53,100 --> 00:07:54,420
 We don't listen to what he says.

198
00:07:54,420 --> 00:07:56,900
 We recall what someone else has said in the past.

199
00:07:56,900 --> 00:07:59,500
 And I'm not telling you to just eject everything

200
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:00,700
 you've learned in the past.

201
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:02,220
 What I am saying is in this moment,

202
00:08:02,220 --> 00:08:04,980
 it would serve you really well to read this story

203
00:08:04,980 --> 00:08:06,620
 with fresh eyes alongside me.

204
00:08:06,620 --> 00:08:07,860
 Does that sound good?

205
00:08:07,860 --> 00:08:10,560
 I want you to look at this text

206
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:14,480
 and understand what it's actually saying,

207
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:18,460
 because we often misunderstand its meaning.

208
00:08:18,460 --> 00:08:21,180
 And so we're just going to walk through it top to bottom.

209
00:08:21,180 --> 00:08:23,580
 And I'm just going to explain to you what's happening.

210
00:08:23,580 --> 00:08:26,320
 If you want to know what's gone wrong,

211
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:29,640
 and if you want to know why do we go wrong,

212
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:32,740
 this is going to tell you.

213
00:08:32,740 --> 00:08:33,580
 Verse one.

214
00:08:33,580 --> 00:08:38,380
 Now the serpent was more crafty

215
00:08:38,380 --> 00:08:40,620
 than any other beast of the field

216
00:08:40,620 --> 00:08:42,660
 that the Lord God had made.

217
00:08:42,660 --> 00:08:45,540
 He said to the woman, did God actually say,

218
00:08:45,540 --> 00:08:48,060
 you shall not eat of any tree in the garden?

219
00:08:48,060 --> 00:08:49,020
 And the woman said to the serpent,

220
00:08:49,020 --> 00:08:50,860
 we may eat of the fruit of the trees in the garden,

221
00:08:50,860 --> 00:08:53,300
 but God said, you shall not eat of the fruit of the tree

222
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:55,060
 that is in the midst of the garden,

223
00:08:55,060 --> 00:08:56,840
 neither shall you touch it.

224
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:58,940
 Why? Lest you die.

225
00:08:58,940 --> 00:09:00,540
 The first thing you need to know

226
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:04,020
 is things go wrong when we forget God's word.

227
00:09:04,020 --> 00:09:08,940
 Things go wrong when we forget God's word.

228
00:09:08,940 --> 00:09:10,260
 Like right out of the gate.

229
00:09:10,260 --> 00:09:12,260
 Once we start reading through this story,

230
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:13,860
 there's a few things that pop up

231
00:09:13,860 --> 00:09:16,560
 and should appear odd to us, should seem strange.

232
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:19,500
 Some signal flares should be firing off

233
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:22,240
 into the atmosphere of your intellect.

234
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:25,620
 And the reason why is because we see not just the woman,

235
00:09:25,620 --> 00:09:29,740
 but we see the snake both misrepresent what God has said

236
00:09:29,740 --> 00:09:31,700
 in the stories that we've already read

237
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:33,120
 through Genesis one and Genesis two.

238
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:36,980
 They do not correctly identify his commands,

239
00:09:36,980 --> 00:09:40,100
 which begs the question then, what were God's commands?

240
00:09:40,100 --> 00:09:42,260
 Well, Genesis two, 16, 17 tells you,

241
00:09:42,260 --> 00:09:43,940
 it's kind of a two part command.

242
00:09:43,940 --> 00:09:46,060
 The first command that God gave is,

243
00:09:46,060 --> 00:09:49,800
 hey, you can eat of every tree in the garden,

244
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:53,920
 which is an amazing command.

245
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:57,580
 Because what it tells us is that God has looked upon Adam

246
00:09:57,580 --> 00:09:58,420
 and Eve and he has said,

247
00:09:58,420 --> 00:10:02,100
 hey, everything in the garden, it's fair game.

248
00:10:02,100 --> 00:10:04,580
 Like you can get out there and you can take your pick.

249
00:10:04,580 --> 00:10:05,540
 You can literally,

250
00:10:05,540 --> 00:10:08,120
 you can enter into the proverbial grocery store

251
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:10,180
 and you can pick whatever you want off the shelves.

252
00:10:10,180 --> 00:10:13,180
 And it is not gonna actually add to your waistline.

253
00:10:13,180 --> 00:10:15,500
 It's only going to lead to your joy.

254
00:10:15,500 --> 00:10:17,620
 There's nothing here that you have to earn.

255
00:10:17,620 --> 00:10:19,860
 Everything here is freely given.

256
00:10:19,860 --> 00:10:21,500
 How amazing is that?

257
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:24,020
 Then there's a second part.

258
00:10:24,020 --> 00:10:25,580
 The second part of the command is,

259
00:10:25,580 --> 00:10:28,660
 but just don't eat of one tree.

260
00:10:28,660 --> 00:10:31,820
 Don't eat of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil.

261
00:10:31,820 --> 00:10:32,660
 Why God?

262
00:10:32,660 --> 00:10:34,300
 Because then you'll die.

263
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:35,120
 It's funny.

264
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:40,120
 We read that command and what we often hear is God say,

265
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:44,140
 but do not eat of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil

266
00:10:44,140 --> 00:10:45,940
 or I'll kill you.

267
00:10:45,940 --> 00:10:47,920
 That's not what actually is said here.

268
00:10:47,920 --> 00:10:50,360
 What's said here is you'll die.

269
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:53,460
 God is not coming to us and saying,

270
00:10:53,460 --> 00:10:56,060
 hey, you need to perform for my approval.

271
00:10:56,060 --> 00:10:56,900
 That's not what he's saying.

272
00:10:56,900 --> 00:10:59,700
 He's saying, no, joy is fully available to you.

273
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,700
 This is not about being performative.

274
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:03,340
 This is about being preventative.

275
00:11:03,340 --> 00:11:06,620
 God is saying, hey, there is a whole world for you to enjoy

276
00:11:06,620 --> 00:11:09,220
 all of this goodness that I have blessed you with.

277
00:11:09,220 --> 00:11:11,860
 And yet there's one thing that'll mess it up.

278
00:11:11,860 --> 00:11:13,080
 So just don't do that.

279
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:18,800
 God's first command, it's not a prohibition to your joy.

280
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:22,060
 It's an invitation to joy.

281
00:11:22,060 --> 00:11:24,940
 That's what God is inviting Adam and Eve into

282
00:11:24,940 --> 00:11:27,660
 from the very beginning of the story.

283
00:11:27,660 --> 00:11:32,660
 And yet look at the way that the snake twists God's command.

284
00:11:34,180 --> 00:11:36,500
 He says, did God actually say

285
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:39,380
 you shall not eat of any tree in the garden?

286
00:11:39,380 --> 00:11:40,220
 It's interesting.

287
00:11:40,220 --> 00:11:41,420
 This is the way the enemy works.

288
00:11:41,420 --> 00:11:46,060
 He doesn't need you to start by just denying God.

289
00:11:46,060 --> 00:11:50,640
 He needs you to start by just doubting him.

290
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:53,500
 He just wants you to see

291
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:56,900
 that there might be something else available on the table.

292
00:11:56,900 --> 00:11:58,480
 He doesn't need you to just reject God.

293
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:01,040
 That'd be a really hard sell, but because he's crafty,

294
00:12:01,040 --> 00:12:02,540
 what he does is he looks at you and he says,

295
00:12:02,540 --> 00:12:03,500
 no, you don't have to reject God,

296
00:12:03,500 --> 00:12:05,420
 but I do want you to accept sin.

297
00:12:05,420 --> 00:12:11,460
 He doesn't approach Eve with a smoking vial of poison,

298
00:12:11,460 --> 00:12:13,660
 taking drink, you know, that's not what he does.

299
00:12:13,660 --> 00:12:14,740
 He comes to her with what?

300
00:12:14,740 --> 00:12:18,260
 Something that is delightful, that is pleasing to the eye.

301
00:12:18,260 --> 00:12:22,180
 He comes in and he presents an option

302
00:12:22,180 --> 00:12:25,340
 that appears satisfying.

303
00:12:25,340 --> 00:12:30,100
 And what we see is that as she accepts sin,

304
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:34,140
 she takes the first step in forgetting God.

305
00:12:34,140 --> 00:12:36,780
 Because we can just read her words

306
00:12:36,780 --> 00:12:38,020
 and we can see that that's true.

307
00:12:38,020 --> 00:12:38,860
 What are her words?

308
00:12:38,860 --> 00:12:42,620
 Her words are, you shall not eat of the tree in the midst

309
00:12:42,620 --> 00:12:43,860
 or in the middle of the garden.

310
00:12:43,860 --> 00:12:45,940
 That's what she responds to the snake with,

311
00:12:45,940 --> 00:12:48,780
 which is incorrect, why?

312
00:12:48,780 --> 00:12:51,300
 Because the tree of the knowledge of good and evil,

313
00:12:51,300 --> 00:12:53,460
 according to God's estimation,

314
00:12:53,460 --> 00:12:55,680
 is not in the middle of the garden.

315
00:12:55,680 --> 00:13:00,680
 God has said that the tree of life

316
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:02,920
 is in the middle of the garden.

317
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:05,540
 The tree of the knowledge of good and evil is nearby,

318
00:13:05,540 --> 00:13:10,020
 but God distinctly identifies the tree of life

319
00:13:10,020 --> 00:13:11,180
 as the middle of his garden.

320
00:13:11,180 --> 00:13:14,660
 But for Eve, the tree of the knowledge of good and evil

321
00:13:14,660 --> 00:13:16,520
 is the center of her garden.

322
00:13:16,520 --> 00:13:19,100
 It's the middle of her affection.

323
00:13:19,100 --> 00:13:22,740
 It is the orbit around all of her attention.

324
00:13:22,740 --> 00:13:23,940
 Why is that?

325
00:13:23,940 --> 00:13:26,260
 Well, it tells us something really important

326
00:13:26,260 --> 00:13:27,980
 about human nature.

327
00:13:27,980 --> 00:13:31,920
 We are so very quick to forget all that God has given.

328
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:37,060
 And we are so very quick to focus on all that he hasn't.

329
00:13:37,060 --> 00:13:39,420
 Don't we do this?

330
00:13:39,420 --> 00:13:41,780
 Don't we focus on what we don't have

331
00:13:41,780 --> 00:13:43,940
 as opposed to what we do have?

332
00:13:43,940 --> 00:13:46,360
 Got a great job,

333
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:48,780
 but I don't have a boyfriend or a girlfriend.

334
00:13:48,780 --> 00:13:52,560
 Man, I got an amazing personality, but I hate my body.

335
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:54,300
 Man, I've got people that love me, support me,

336
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:55,140
 are cheering for me,

337
00:13:55,140 --> 00:13:56,100
 but they're not the right kind of people.

338
00:13:56,100 --> 00:13:57,740
 I wanna be with those people instead.

339
00:13:57,740 --> 00:13:59,660
 You see how this works?

340
00:13:59,660 --> 00:14:00,680
 Figure it out for yourself.

341
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:01,700
 We all do this.

342
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:03,300
 We all look at what we have

343
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:05,520
 and we identify it as insufficient.

344
00:14:05,520 --> 00:14:06,580
 We want something else.

345
00:14:06,580 --> 00:14:08,220
 We want something more.

346
00:14:08,220 --> 00:14:09,920
 And I think, and that's important.

347
00:14:09,920 --> 00:14:12,380
 I think this, I don't actually see this

348
00:14:12,380 --> 00:14:13,300
 clearly from the text

349
00:14:13,300 --> 00:14:15,260
 'cause it doesn't tell us explicitly,

350
00:14:15,260 --> 00:14:18,300
 but I do think that what we get an eye into

351
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:20,220
 from this specific moment,

352
00:14:20,220 --> 00:14:22,940
 as Eve has centered her attention

353
00:14:22,940 --> 00:14:24,420
 on the tree of the knowledge of good and evil

354
00:14:24,420 --> 00:14:25,980
 as being in the middle of her garden,

355
00:14:25,980 --> 00:14:28,940
 what we see is a heart of ingratitude springing up,

356
00:14:28,940 --> 00:14:34,100
 which is the root, the first step to all sin.

357
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:39,260
 It's an ungrateful heart, which begs the question,

358
00:14:39,260 --> 00:14:41,180
 where in your heart are you ungrateful

359
00:14:41,180 --> 00:14:42,920
 for what God has given?

360
00:14:42,920 --> 00:14:44,700
 The second thing that we see her say,

361
00:14:44,700 --> 00:14:46,660
 which helps us to understand that,

362
00:14:46,660 --> 00:14:49,660
 man, she is actually forgetting God's word,

363
00:14:49,660 --> 00:14:52,380
 is she says, "Neither shall you touch it,"

364
00:14:52,380 --> 00:14:55,300
 which isn't just a misunderstanding of what God has said.

365
00:14:55,300 --> 00:14:58,060
 It's actually not even included in God's command.

366
00:14:58,060 --> 00:14:59,360
 God never said that.

367
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:02,940
 It's an addition that she adds onto what God has said.

368
00:15:02,940 --> 00:15:04,960
 It's interesting when you read through the Bible,

369
00:15:04,960 --> 00:15:06,820
 the Pharisees, which were the religious leaders

370
00:15:06,820 --> 00:15:10,940
 of Jesus' day, those guys who were most biblically informed,

371
00:15:10,940 --> 00:15:14,300
 they were the ones that were notoriously bad at this.

372
00:15:14,300 --> 00:15:18,020
 They were horrible about adding things onto God's word.

373
00:15:18,020 --> 00:15:20,000
 They actually rabbinically had these things

374
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,060
 known as fence laws.

375
00:15:21,060 --> 00:15:22,540
 Fence laws, there were hundreds,

376
00:15:22,540 --> 00:15:26,180
 if not thousands of these laws that serve to protect them

377
00:15:26,180 --> 00:15:29,460
 from going too far, disobeying God's word.

378
00:15:29,460 --> 00:15:31,060
 And yet for fear of going too far, you know what they did?

379
00:15:31,060 --> 00:15:32,460
 They never went far enough.

380
00:15:32,460 --> 00:15:36,460
 Too often, this happens to Christians,

381
00:15:36,460 --> 00:15:38,660
 particularly good Christians.

382
00:15:38,660 --> 00:15:41,140
 We find ourselves, for fear of going too far,

383
00:15:41,140 --> 00:15:43,680
 not going far enough.

384
00:15:43,680 --> 00:15:45,520
 We become legalistic.

385
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:49,780
 We start thinking about what we do and what we don't do,

386
00:15:49,780 --> 00:15:51,580
 as opposed to what God has done.

387
00:15:52,420 --> 00:15:54,140
 And as a result, you know what it does?

388
00:15:54,140 --> 00:15:56,440
 It evokes within the spirit of a person,

389
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:59,460
 this deep fear of losing this life that I have,

390
00:15:59,460 --> 00:16:02,360
 as opposed to enjoying the life that God has come to give.

391
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:06,380
 These are Eve's two mistakes.

392
00:16:06,380 --> 00:16:08,560
 She has fallen prey to a very dangerous trap.

393
00:16:08,560 --> 00:16:09,460
 You want to know what the trap is?

394
00:16:09,460 --> 00:16:12,740
 The trap is she knows just enough about God,

395
00:16:12,740 --> 00:16:16,880
 which is something we so very often fall into ourselves.

396
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:22,540
 Like we know enough about God to believe in him,

397
00:16:22,540 --> 00:16:24,980
 to claim the identity of Christian,

398
00:16:24,980 --> 00:16:27,540
 but we don't know enough about Jesus

399
00:16:27,540 --> 00:16:29,720
 to know what we actually believe,

400
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:32,780
 to actually articulate the gospel.

401
00:16:32,780 --> 00:16:36,140
 We know enough about God to love him,

402
00:16:36,140 --> 00:16:38,820
 but we don't know enough about God

403
00:16:38,820 --> 00:16:42,060
 to give all of our life to him,

404
00:16:42,060 --> 00:16:44,360
 to surrender our every affection,

405
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:45,720
 to make sure that there's no part of us

406
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:47,180
 that's divided in any other place,

407
00:16:47,180 --> 00:16:50,860
 but is totally united in loving him and him alone.

408
00:16:50,860 --> 00:16:53,120
 We know enough about God to trust him,

409
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:56,760
 but we don't know enough about God

410
00:16:56,760 --> 00:17:01,760
 to surrender every single inch of our life.

411
00:17:01,760 --> 00:17:05,980
 There are things we hold back,

412
00:17:05,980 --> 00:17:08,020
 pieces of ourselves we don't want him to touch,

413
00:17:08,020 --> 00:17:11,220
 because though we say we do, we don't actually trust him.

414
00:17:11,220 --> 00:17:14,720
 We know just enough about God

415
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:17,140
 to be dangerous at this whole Christian thing,

416
00:17:17,140 --> 00:17:19,260
 but we don't know enough about God

417
00:17:19,260 --> 00:17:22,220
 to keep ourselves from being a danger to ourselves.

418
00:17:22,220 --> 00:17:27,360
 Psalm 119, verse nine, it says this.

419
00:17:27,360 --> 00:17:31,880
 "How can a young man or woman keep their way pure?

420
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:34,540
 By guarding it."

421
00:17:34,540 --> 00:17:35,380
 According to what?

422
00:17:35,380 --> 00:17:36,820
 "To your word.

423
00:17:36,820 --> 00:17:39,820
 With my whole heart, I seek you.

424
00:17:39,820 --> 00:17:41,580
 Let me not wander from your commandments.

425
00:17:41,580 --> 00:17:43,440
 I've stored up your word in my heart

426
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:44,860
 that I might not sin against you."

427
00:17:44,860 --> 00:17:46,160
 Do you hear it?

428
00:17:46,160 --> 00:17:48,460
 That kind of ferocious faith

429
00:17:48,460 --> 00:17:51,480
 that depends wholeheartedly on the words of God?

430
00:17:51,480 --> 00:17:53,000
 So let me ask you something,

431
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:54,940
 'cause I think that this is a helpful litmus test.

432
00:17:54,940 --> 00:17:56,960
 Whenever your life goes sideways,

433
00:17:56,960 --> 00:18:00,280
 whenever things just kind of fall off the normal path

434
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:02,540
 and things become very, very difficult,

435
00:18:02,540 --> 00:18:04,040
 what comes out of you?

436
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:07,180
 Like whenever you get fired unexpectedly,

437
00:18:07,180 --> 00:18:08,220
 what's your natural response?

438
00:18:08,220 --> 00:18:10,940
 Whenever that guy whom you've been dating for years

439
00:18:10,940 --> 00:18:12,580
 at this point breaks up with you

440
00:18:12,580 --> 00:18:14,260
 instead of going into marriage with you,

441
00:18:14,260 --> 00:18:17,720
 what comes out of you whenever you find some loved one,

442
00:18:17,720 --> 00:18:19,740
 a family member, a dear friend comes down

443
00:18:19,740 --> 00:18:22,560
 with some sort of a fatal diagnosis?

444
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:24,000
 What comes out of you?

445
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:29,620
 Jesus faced

446
00:18:29,620 --> 00:18:37,720
 the three most pressure-packed moments in his story.

447
00:18:37,720 --> 00:18:44,000
 Tempted in the wilderness before he began his ministry.

448
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,620
 Garden of Gethsemane, the night of his arrest,

449
00:18:47,620 --> 00:18:50,860
 and Calvary, dying for the sins of the world.

450
00:18:50,860 --> 00:18:52,860
 And you wanna know what came out of him?

451
00:18:52,860 --> 00:18:55,460
 The words of God.

452
00:18:55,460 --> 00:19:02,260
 Virtually every single word he spoke

453
00:19:02,260 --> 00:19:05,260
 in those moments that were most pressure-packed,

454
00:19:05,260 --> 00:19:09,500
 they were God's words.

455
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:12,900
 Why?

456
00:19:15,260 --> 00:19:17,860
 Not because he's just trying to fulfill prophecy.

457
00:19:17,860 --> 00:19:20,940
 He does that, that's true.

458
00:19:20,940 --> 00:19:24,220
 He does fulfill prophecy in the process

459
00:19:24,220 --> 00:19:26,860
 of saying these things amidst these difficulties,

460
00:19:26,860 --> 00:19:28,020
 but that's not why he does it.

461
00:19:28,020 --> 00:19:29,820
 He does it, he speaks these things

462
00:19:29,820 --> 00:19:32,700
 'cause out of the overflow of the heart, guess what?

463
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:35,220
 The mouth is gonna speak.

464
00:19:35,220 --> 00:19:39,020
 He speaks out what he has engraved on his mind.

465
00:19:39,020 --> 00:19:41,980
 God has etched into his heart the very person

466
00:19:41,980 --> 00:19:45,580
 that he has become as he has walked with God.

467
00:19:45,580 --> 00:19:48,700
 That person is particularly exposed

468
00:19:48,700 --> 00:19:50,880
 in those moments of greatest difficulty.

469
00:19:50,880 --> 00:19:55,780
 You see, Jesus knew things go wrong

470
00:19:55,780 --> 00:19:57,780
 when we forget God's word,

471
00:19:57,780 --> 00:20:00,380
 but things go right when we remember it.

472
00:20:00,380 --> 00:20:03,580
 That's the first one.

473
00:20:03,580 --> 00:20:04,940
 Look at verse four.

474
00:20:04,940 --> 00:20:07,880
 "But the serpent," she said to the," she, it's not a she.

475
00:20:07,880 --> 00:20:09,460
 "The serpent said to the woman,

476
00:20:09,460 --> 00:20:11,620
 "you will not surely die for God knows

477
00:20:11,620 --> 00:20:13,660
 "that when you eat of it, your eyes will be opened

478
00:20:13,660 --> 00:20:16,020
 "and you'll be like God, knowing good and evil."

479
00:20:16,020 --> 00:20:17,500
 So the second thing you gotta know

480
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:20,740
 is that things go wrong when we question God's character.

481
00:20:20,740 --> 00:20:22,740
 Things go wrong when we question God's character.

482
00:20:22,740 --> 00:20:24,900
 It's a really subtle detail mentioned in here,

483
00:20:24,900 --> 00:20:28,100
 but we talked last week about how,

484
00:20:28,100 --> 00:20:29,520
 over the course of chapter two and chapter three,

485
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:32,380
 which is actually the narrative

486
00:20:32,380 --> 00:20:33,780
 that we're a part of in this moment.

487
00:20:33,780 --> 00:20:36,980
 One is the creation story from like 50,000 feet.

488
00:20:36,980 --> 00:20:38,440
 It's up at God's level.

489
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:41,160
 It's seeing everything come to be all at once.

490
00:20:41,160 --> 00:20:42,940
 And yet when you get to Genesis two,

491
00:20:42,940 --> 00:20:45,180
 it's again, a different vantage point.

492
00:20:45,180 --> 00:20:47,260
 Like if you were watching instant replay on the Superbowl,

493
00:20:47,260 --> 00:20:48,860
 you might get one angle to show one side

494
00:20:48,860 --> 00:20:50,480
 and then a different angle to show a different side.

495
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:53,340
 Genesis two is a different angle to the same story.

496
00:20:53,340 --> 00:20:56,380
 And what we see as we zoom specifically in on humanity

497
00:20:56,380 --> 00:20:58,980
 is that story continues into chapter three.

498
00:20:58,980 --> 00:21:00,600
 As we move into chapter three,

499
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:03,800
 we see a pattern that was established last week.

500
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:06,420
 That pattern is that Moses who authored this book

501
00:21:06,420 --> 00:21:08,540
 talks about God in a twofold title.

502
00:21:08,540 --> 00:21:13,540
 He calls him Lord God 20 times, like on repeat.

503
00:21:13,540 --> 00:21:16,700
 Like he hit that button mistakenly on Spotify

504
00:21:16,700 --> 00:21:17,540
 and the song just keeps playing

505
00:21:17,540 --> 00:21:18,740
 over and over and over and over again.

506
00:21:18,740 --> 00:21:19,820
 That's what's happening right here.

507
00:21:19,820 --> 00:21:22,580
 He calls him Lord God or Elohim Yahweh.

508
00:21:22,580 --> 00:21:23,820
 It's a twofold title.

509
00:21:23,820 --> 00:21:25,540
 It's a bundle deal.

510
00:21:25,540 --> 00:21:27,980
 And yet though that happens 20 times

511
00:21:27,980 --> 00:21:30,020
 as the particular title of God,

512
00:21:30,020 --> 00:21:31,820
 you know what pops up in this story?

513
00:21:31,820 --> 00:21:34,380
 A different title.

514
00:21:34,380 --> 00:21:39,380
 And that title is not Elohim Yahweh, it's Elohim.

515
00:21:39,380 --> 00:21:43,860
 And guess who calls him that?

516
00:21:43,860 --> 00:21:46,020
 The serpent.

517
00:21:46,020 --> 00:21:51,360
 The serpent takes Lord God and throws out the Lord

518
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:54,580
 and just calls him God because what he's trying to do

519
00:21:54,580 --> 00:21:57,380
 is he is trying to impersonalize

520
00:21:57,380 --> 00:21:59,860
 the character of God to Eve.

521
00:21:59,860 --> 00:22:01,140
 He wants her to know, hey,

522
00:22:01,140 --> 00:22:04,060
 that caring and covenantal nature,

523
00:22:04,060 --> 00:22:05,820
 all that is good and represented

524
00:22:05,820 --> 00:22:10,300
 in the personal intimate identity of God through Yahweh,

525
00:22:10,300 --> 00:22:12,580
 don't pay attention to that.

526
00:22:12,580 --> 00:22:15,500
 Just focus instead on the fact that he's transcendent.

527
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:16,660
 He's all powerful.

528
00:22:16,660 --> 00:22:18,520
 He's distant and he's disinterested.

529
00:22:18,520 --> 00:22:21,140
 Sure, he's in control of things,

530
00:22:21,140 --> 00:22:23,780
 but he doesn't really care what's happening in your life.

531
00:22:23,780 --> 00:22:27,180
 He's not really holding you to the things that he said.

532
00:22:27,180 --> 00:22:30,020
 He's far off and not paying attention right now.

533
00:22:30,020 --> 00:22:32,380
 He is all powerful, but he's not all personal.

534
00:22:32,380 --> 00:22:33,540
 Don't worry about that.

535
00:22:35,060 --> 00:22:36,740
 Why does he do it?

536
00:22:36,740 --> 00:22:44,320
 Because he wants to render God as an impersonal God.

537
00:22:44,320 --> 00:22:48,060
 I remember years ago, applied for this job,

538
00:22:48,060 --> 00:22:49,660
 was really excited for the opportunity.

539
00:22:49,660 --> 00:22:50,620
 It was a great organization.

540
00:22:50,620 --> 00:22:51,740
 I knew some of the people that worked there,

541
00:22:51,740 --> 00:22:53,680
 was thinking this was going to be a great next step.

542
00:22:53,680 --> 00:22:55,660
 And yet, though I knew some people,

543
00:22:55,660 --> 00:22:58,120
 I got rejected not by way of a phone call.

544
00:22:58,120 --> 00:22:59,900
 I got rejected by way of an email.

545
00:22:59,900 --> 00:23:00,820
 Anybody been there?

546
00:23:00,820 --> 00:23:03,700
 And what happens in that moment is it feels cold

547
00:23:03,700 --> 00:23:05,140
 and it feels calculated.

548
00:23:05,140 --> 00:23:07,640
 And though we had a relationship,

549
00:23:07,640 --> 00:23:09,340
 some distrust came out of me.

550
00:23:09,340 --> 00:23:11,940
 I started to feel a kind of way about these people.

551
00:23:11,940 --> 00:23:13,420
 Why?

552
00:23:13,420 --> 00:23:15,660
 Because it lacked a personal touch.

553
00:23:15,660 --> 00:23:19,920
 The serpent, he wants Eve.

554
00:23:19,920 --> 00:23:24,920
 And Satan, he wants you to forget the personal touch of God.

555
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:28,420
 He wants you to question his character.

556
00:23:28,420 --> 00:23:32,580
 And yet what we know is God's question,

557
00:23:32,580 --> 00:23:34,100
 or God's character is not in question.

558
00:23:34,100 --> 00:23:35,540
 And the reason we know it is because there's a couple

559
00:23:35,540 --> 00:23:37,920
 of reasons specifically in these two verses.

560
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:40,180
 The first is found in that false promise

561
00:23:40,180 --> 00:23:41,300
 that the serpent gives Eve.

562
00:23:41,300 --> 00:23:45,500
 He says, "Once you eat of it, you'll be like God."

563
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:48,900
 Here's the sad irony of that false promise.

564
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:51,980
 She's already like God.

565
00:23:51,980 --> 00:23:57,820
 That was declared by God in the last two chapters.

566
00:23:57,820 --> 00:24:00,300
 He looked at her and he said in Genesis 1, 26,

567
00:24:00,300 --> 00:24:03,580
 "Let us make man in our image, after our likeness,

568
00:24:03,580 --> 00:24:06,180
 male and female, he created them."

569
00:24:06,180 --> 00:24:08,900
 Like Eve has failed to remember

570
00:24:08,900 --> 00:24:12,460
 that a God-given identity is not something you achieve.

571
00:24:12,460 --> 00:24:14,580
 It is something you receive.

572
00:24:14,580 --> 00:24:17,060
 It is something that you cannot do anything to earn.

573
00:24:17,060 --> 00:24:18,300
 You cannot say anything to earn.

574
00:24:18,300 --> 00:24:19,500
 You cannot think anything to earn.

575
00:24:19,500 --> 00:24:21,340
 No place you can go to actually earn it.

576
00:24:21,340 --> 00:24:25,760
 Instead, it's everything that God has done instead.

577
00:24:25,760 --> 00:24:28,540
 You see, this is so tragic.

578
00:24:28,540 --> 00:24:31,940
 Like in Adam and Eve's effort to become like God,

579
00:24:31,940 --> 00:24:34,660
 they become less like God.

580
00:24:34,660 --> 00:24:37,540
 They become more like the serpent.

581
00:24:37,540 --> 00:24:41,100
 They decide for themselves what is good, what is not good.

582
00:24:41,100 --> 00:24:42,900
 They choose their own way.

583
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:47,020
 And in the process of doing so, they become sinful.

584
00:24:47,020 --> 00:24:49,980
 The second reason we know that God's character

585
00:24:49,980 --> 00:24:54,380
 is not in question here is because though Adam and Eve

586
00:24:54,380 --> 00:24:58,080
 wanted to know the knowledge of good and evil,

587
00:24:59,340 --> 00:25:00,780
 there's no implication here

588
00:25:00,780 --> 00:25:03,220
 that God never intended to teach them that.

589
00:25:03,220 --> 00:25:05,020
 Actually, according to ancient tradition,

590
00:25:05,020 --> 00:25:09,400
 there's a widely held belief that God did want to teach them

591
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:10,660
 the knowledge of good and evil,

592
00:25:10,660 --> 00:25:13,020
 what the scripture also articulates as wisdom.

593
00:25:13,020 --> 00:25:15,500
 And we know it's true that God does want to teach us wisdom

594
00:25:15,500 --> 00:25:17,740
 because James 1 tells us in verses five and six,

595
00:25:17,740 --> 00:25:20,100
 if any of you lacks wisdom, guess what?

596
00:25:20,100 --> 00:25:21,660
 Just ask God.

597
00:25:21,660 --> 00:25:24,060
 He gives it generously to all without reproach

598
00:25:24,060 --> 00:25:24,900
 and it will be given him,

599
00:25:24,900 --> 00:25:28,740
 but let him ask in faith with no doubting.

600
00:25:28,740 --> 00:25:30,820
 For the one who doubts is like a wave of the sea

601
00:25:30,820 --> 00:25:33,380
 that is driven and tossed by the wind.

602
00:25:33,380 --> 00:25:36,140
 You see, God gives wisdom to those that do not doubt,

603
00:25:36,140 --> 00:25:37,740
 that don't question his character.

604
00:25:37,740 --> 00:25:40,260
 So let me ask you, because I think this is gonna hit home.

605
00:25:40,260 --> 00:25:44,200
 Why then do we question God's character?

606
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:48,420
 Why do we seek wisdom on our own?

607
00:25:48,420 --> 00:25:50,100
 We know, man, he gives it freely

608
00:25:51,940 --> 00:25:55,180
 because he often does not give us wisdom nearly

609
00:25:55,180 --> 00:25:56,340
 as quick as we want it.

610
00:25:56,340 --> 00:26:00,460
 That's what happens to them.

611
00:26:00,460 --> 00:26:04,260
 They don't want it later, they want it now.

612
00:26:04,260 --> 00:26:05,700
 And some of you, you can relate to that

613
00:26:05,700 --> 00:26:08,400
 because you're dealing with the thought that man,

614
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:10,100
 the things that you want from God,

615
00:26:10,100 --> 00:26:13,000
 they're taking too long for them to actually be loving.

616
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:17,620
 Getting over the loss of a loved one,

617
00:26:17,620 --> 00:26:19,440
 moving on from the betrayal of a friend,

618
00:26:19,440 --> 00:26:22,220
 dealing with the difficulty of being single.

619
00:26:22,220 --> 00:26:23,280
 I don't know what it is for you,

620
00:26:23,280 --> 00:26:25,660
 but whatever it is for you, what you need to realize

621
00:26:25,660 --> 00:26:27,940
 is that often the fastest route to your happiness

622
00:26:27,940 --> 00:26:29,320
 is not the wisest route.

623
00:26:29,320 --> 00:26:32,140
 God might have you in a season of suffering

624
00:26:32,140 --> 00:26:35,580
 because he wants to walk with you through that season

625
00:26:35,580 --> 00:26:40,580
 and help you learn not just who you are, but who he is.

626
00:26:40,580 --> 00:26:44,340
 That's what we see in Romans 5.

627
00:26:44,340 --> 00:26:45,180
 He says, "Not only that,

628
00:26:45,180 --> 00:26:47,140
 "but we rejoice in what in our sufferings."

629
00:26:47,140 --> 00:26:48,440
 We rejoice in our sufferings.

630
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:51,200
 What a crazy idea, knowing that suffering,

631
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:52,660
 it actually produces endurance.

632
00:26:52,660 --> 00:26:54,020
 And endurance, it produces character.

633
00:26:54,020 --> 00:26:55,340
 And character, it produces hope.

634
00:26:55,340 --> 00:26:57,620
 And hope, it doesn't put us to shame

635
00:26:57,620 --> 00:27:01,900
 because God's love has been poured into our hearts

636
00:27:01,900 --> 00:27:04,600
 through the Holy Spirit who has been given to us.

637
00:27:04,600 --> 00:27:08,980
 That's why we trust God.

638
00:27:08,980 --> 00:27:12,260
 We trust God because he has poured his love into our hearts.

639
00:27:12,260 --> 00:27:13,820
 And yet the knowledge of that love,

640
00:27:13,820 --> 00:27:15,280
 it does not come without suffering.

641
00:27:15,280 --> 00:27:18,100
 It comes through suffering.

642
00:27:18,100 --> 00:27:19,820
 It's fascinating to me.

643
00:27:19,820 --> 00:27:23,740
 Recently, I was watching this reel on YouTube

644
00:27:23,740 --> 00:27:27,220
 and it was doing a before and after on drill sergeants.

645
00:27:27,220 --> 00:27:28,260
 And they would start talking.

646
00:27:28,260 --> 00:27:30,540
 And it's like, "Hey guys, my name's whoever.

647
00:27:30,540 --> 00:27:33,100
 "And I'm really excited, thankful to serve my country."

648
00:27:33,100 --> 00:27:35,360
 And then in the after, it was like,

649
00:27:35,360 --> 00:27:37,700
 "My name is whatever.

650
00:27:37,700 --> 00:27:39,440
 "I've yelled a lot over the last several years.

651
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:41,300
 "And so my vocal cords are completely strained."

652
00:27:41,300 --> 00:27:42,980
 It was just like, they were completely different people.

653
00:27:42,980 --> 00:27:46,300
 So I beg the question, why are these guys so hardcore?

654
00:27:46,300 --> 00:27:49,180
 Why is it that over the course of these boot camps,

655
00:27:49,180 --> 00:27:51,780
 they just feel the need to yell at all of these people?

656
00:27:51,780 --> 00:27:56,780
 And the reason why is they know conflict reveals character.

657
00:27:56,780 --> 00:27:59,380
 You go through buds, it's hard.

658
00:27:59,380 --> 00:28:00,900
 You go through pararescue, it's hard.

659
00:28:00,900 --> 00:28:02,660
 You go through ranger camp, it's hard

660
00:28:02,660 --> 00:28:06,140
 because they want to see what people are made of.

661
00:28:06,140 --> 00:28:07,500
 Here's the amazing thing.

662
00:28:07,500 --> 00:28:13,700
 We know what God is made of.

663
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:18,500
 We know his character because he suffered.

664
00:28:18,500 --> 00:28:22,380
 We witnessed by way of the word,

665
00:28:22,380 --> 00:28:25,660
 Christ endure on the cross,

666
00:28:25,660 --> 00:28:28,220
 all of the indulgence of our darkness.

667
00:28:28,220 --> 00:28:31,580
 We saw when we gave up on God, he did not give up on us.

668
00:28:31,580 --> 00:28:32,660
 Whenever we indulge darkness,

669
00:28:32,660 --> 00:28:35,420
 he endured our darkness by way of death.

670
00:28:35,420 --> 00:28:37,900
 We have seen that he is who he says he is.

671
00:28:37,900 --> 00:28:39,780
 He has done what he said he would do.

672
00:28:39,780 --> 00:28:41,340
 He is good.

673
00:28:44,780 --> 00:28:47,020
 Things go wrong when we question God's character,

674
00:28:47,020 --> 00:28:49,400
 but things, they go right when we trust it.

675
00:28:49,400 --> 00:28:52,920
 Thirdly, look at verse six with me.

676
00:28:52,920 --> 00:28:56,620
 So when the woman saw that the tree was good for food,

677
00:28:56,620 --> 00:28:58,500
 that it was a delight to the eyes,

678
00:28:58,500 --> 00:29:00,220
 that the tree was to be desired to make one wise.

679
00:29:00,220 --> 00:29:01,860
 She took of its fruit and she ate,

680
00:29:01,860 --> 00:29:03,560
 and she also gave some of it to her husband

681
00:29:03,560 --> 00:29:05,380
 who was with her and he ate.

682
00:29:05,380 --> 00:29:06,860
 In the eyes of both, they were open

683
00:29:06,860 --> 00:29:09,420
 and they knew that they were naked.

684
00:29:09,420 --> 00:29:10,780
 And they sewed fig leaves together

685
00:29:10,780 --> 00:29:13,460
 and they made themselves loincloths.

686
00:29:13,460 --> 00:29:14,860
 The third thing you need to know

687
00:29:14,860 --> 00:29:17,480
 is things go wrong when we justify sin.

688
00:29:17,480 --> 00:29:22,180
 Things go wrong when we justify sin.

689
00:29:22,180 --> 00:29:23,020
 It's interesting.

690
00:29:23,020 --> 00:29:25,120
 It says that their eyes were open.

691
00:29:25,120 --> 00:29:27,480
 The servant was actually consistent in that promise

692
00:29:27,480 --> 00:29:29,740
 because their eyes were in fact open.

693
00:29:29,740 --> 00:29:32,180
 And as their eyes were open, they realized,

694
00:29:32,180 --> 00:29:35,420
 ah, we're naked, which is kind of a weird detail

695
00:29:35,420 --> 00:29:37,540
 if you read over the course of chapters two and three,

696
00:29:37,540 --> 00:29:40,460
 because it says that they're naked four different times.

697
00:29:40,460 --> 00:29:43,000
 That word naked, it should stand out

698
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:47,200
 as a peculiar piece to the rest of the story.

699
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:48,940
 Again, if we're reading it freshly,

700
00:29:48,940 --> 00:29:50,540
 then we should see it as something

701
00:29:50,540 --> 00:29:53,740
 that is a little bit abnormal.

702
00:29:53,740 --> 00:29:55,300
 We often don't do that.

703
00:29:55,300 --> 00:29:58,740
 But what we need to do is see why is nakedness a theme

704
00:29:58,740 --> 00:30:00,620
 in chapters two and three?

705
00:30:00,620 --> 00:30:01,520
 It causes us to lean in.

706
00:30:01,520 --> 00:30:03,100
 Well, in chapter two, when everything was good,

707
00:30:03,100 --> 00:30:05,660
 there was no problem at all, no sin, head into the world.

708
00:30:05,660 --> 00:30:07,780
 What we know is the husband and the wife,

709
00:30:07,780 --> 00:30:08,940
 they were naked, they were not ashamed.

710
00:30:08,940 --> 00:30:10,800
 For some of you, that's your favorite verse in the Bible,

711
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:12,420
 but it's not supposed to be your favorite verse

712
00:30:12,420 --> 00:30:13,860
 in the Bible for the reason that you're thinking

713
00:30:13,860 --> 00:30:14,820
 it's your favorite verse in the Bible.

714
00:30:14,820 --> 00:30:17,340
 It's in fact, a favorite verse in the Bible,

715
00:30:17,340 --> 00:30:19,660
 because what it's expressing is that there was no shame

716
00:30:19,660 --> 00:30:20,820
 between them.

717
00:30:20,820 --> 00:30:22,380
 They had nothing to hide.

718
00:30:22,380 --> 00:30:23,860
 They were totally safe.

719
00:30:23,860 --> 00:30:26,500
 They could be transparent with one another.

720
00:30:26,500 --> 00:30:29,820
 They had vulnerability in relationship to each other.

721
00:30:29,820 --> 00:30:31,280
 Doesn't that sound amazing?

722
00:30:31,280 --> 00:30:37,360
 Having safety in a relationship.

723
00:30:37,360 --> 00:30:40,740
 That's what chapter two talks about.

724
00:30:40,740 --> 00:30:43,120
 And yet when you get to chapter three, that word naked,

725
00:30:43,120 --> 00:30:44,340
 it pops up three more times.

726
00:30:44,340 --> 00:30:46,420
 And yet every time it does,

727
00:30:46,420 --> 00:30:50,060
 their relationship to shame has changed.

728
00:30:50,060 --> 00:30:54,300
 Where they didn't have anything to hide from,

729
00:30:54,300 --> 00:30:56,860
 now they have good reason to hide.

730
00:30:56,860 --> 00:30:58,360
 Where they had nothing to be ashamed of,

731
00:30:58,360 --> 00:31:01,860
 now they feel a deep sense of shame.

732
00:31:01,860 --> 00:31:04,060
 Where they once were totally vulnerable,

733
00:31:04,060 --> 00:31:06,100
 now they're closed off and concealed.

734
00:31:06,100 --> 00:31:10,820
 They don't want to be totally exposed to the other.

735
00:31:10,820 --> 00:31:11,660
 Why?

736
00:31:11,660 --> 00:31:12,900
 Like, why does that happen to them?

737
00:31:12,900 --> 00:31:14,180
 Why the massive change?

738
00:31:14,180 --> 00:31:15,220
 You wanna know why?

739
00:31:15,220 --> 00:31:17,900
 They looked at that stupid fruit for too long.

740
00:31:17,900 --> 00:31:22,680
 They entertained temptation.

741
00:31:22,680 --> 00:31:24,860
 That's what we see.

742
00:31:24,860 --> 00:31:28,600
 Like, it says that Eve, she doesn't just take the fruit,

743
00:31:28,600 --> 00:31:31,260
 it says that she notices the fruit.

744
00:31:31,260 --> 00:31:33,840
 We're gonna talk about what she notices,

745
00:31:33,840 --> 00:31:36,620
 but here's why it's significant for us to understand.

746
00:31:36,620 --> 00:31:38,420
 Sin is never a flip of a switch,

747
00:31:38,420 --> 00:31:41,360
 it's always a slide into depravity.

748
00:31:41,360 --> 00:31:43,620
 Like I was joking with my team,

749
00:31:43,620 --> 00:31:45,520
 nobody goes and serves at the local food bank

750
00:31:45,520 --> 00:31:47,060
 and the next thing you know, hops in the car

751
00:31:47,060 --> 00:31:49,340
 and starts trolling everybody on the internet.

752
00:31:49,340 --> 00:31:50,180
 That doesn't happen.

753
00:31:50,180 --> 00:31:51,000
 Why?

754
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:52,420
 Because that would just be kind of a misappropriation

755
00:31:52,420 --> 00:31:53,260
 of priority.

756
00:31:53,260 --> 00:31:55,020
 It would feel like, man, you're just a completely,

757
00:31:55,020 --> 00:31:58,660
 it'd be a false, it would be an absolute division

758
00:31:58,660 --> 00:32:01,180
 between your character in one place and your character

759
00:32:01,180 --> 00:32:02,000
 in another.

760
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:03,620
 We don't do that.

761
00:32:03,620 --> 00:32:06,180
 What instead happens is we slide into sin.

762
00:32:06,180 --> 00:32:07,860
 James 1, 14, 15 says,

763
00:32:07,860 --> 00:32:11,780
 "But each person is tempted when he's lured

764
00:32:11,780 --> 00:32:14,040
 "and enticed by his own desire.

765
00:32:14,040 --> 00:32:16,720
 "Then desire, when it's conceived, it gives birth to sin,

766
00:32:16,720 --> 00:32:19,520
 "and sin, when it's fully grown, it brings forth death."

767
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:25,020
 I think that word lured is so helpful

768
00:32:25,020 --> 00:32:28,260
 because it just, it paints this picture

769
00:32:28,260 --> 00:32:31,900
 of putting out bait to entice a Christian

770
00:32:31,900 --> 00:32:33,780
 to do what a Christian should not do.

771
00:32:33,780 --> 00:32:37,520
 The image here is of throwing out a lure.

772
00:32:37,520 --> 00:32:39,140
 What's a lure do whenever it's appealing

773
00:32:39,140 --> 00:32:40,300
 to the appetite of a fish?

774
00:32:40,300 --> 00:32:43,020
 It shines and it splashes and it swims.

775
00:32:43,020 --> 00:32:44,460
 That's what sin does to you.

776
00:32:44,460 --> 00:32:47,780
 It splashes and shines and it swims in such a way

777
00:32:47,780 --> 00:32:50,940
 that it appeals to your carnality, your appetite,

778
00:32:50,940 --> 00:32:53,580
 until you actually start to move towards it.

779
00:32:53,580 --> 00:32:57,220
 And yet, again, it's not a switch, it's a slide.

780
00:32:57,220 --> 00:32:59,260
 That's why a single scene from a show,

781
00:32:59,260 --> 00:33:02,460
 an advertisement on TV can lead you to pull out your phone

782
00:33:02,460 --> 00:33:04,660
 and kind of look up that girl, that guy on Instagram.

783
00:33:04,660 --> 00:33:05,700
 And then as you look at them, you know what?

784
00:33:05,700 --> 00:33:06,720
 Next thing you know, you're looking up stuff

785
00:33:06,720 --> 00:33:09,700
