 He does see the source of their shame,

1049
00:43:24,900 --> 00:43:27,060
 but he also sees the effect of it.

1050
00:43:27,060 --> 00:43:30,780
 And so he takes care of his kids first.

1051
00:43:30,780 --> 00:43:32,420
 He starts asking them questions.

1052
00:43:32,420 --> 00:43:34,260
 Some of the questions I think he may be asking you tonight,

1053
00:43:34,260 --> 00:43:36,980
 he asks them, "Hey, where are you?"

1054
00:43:39,040 --> 00:43:40,360
 Where are you?

1055
00:43:40,360 --> 00:43:46,300
 He wants them to know that even when they're lost,

1056
00:43:46,300 --> 00:43:48,420
 he will still seek them in their hiding.

1057
00:43:48,420 --> 00:43:51,880
 He asks them, "Who told you?"

1058
00:43:51,880 --> 00:43:54,480
 He wants them to know that even when you're misled,

1059
00:43:54,480 --> 00:43:57,220
 he'll speak to them what's true.

1060
00:43:57,220 --> 00:44:00,900
 And he asks, "What have you done?"

1061
00:44:00,900 --> 00:44:04,060
 Because he wants them to know that even when they're guilty,

1062
00:44:04,060 --> 00:44:06,700
 he'll still save them from their sin.

1063
00:44:06,700 --> 00:44:08,820
 Don't you see, and this is big.

1064
00:44:08,820 --> 00:44:10,980
 This is what Genesis 3 is about.

1065
00:44:10,980 --> 00:44:15,700
 God's fundamental response to human failure,

1066
00:44:15,700 --> 00:44:20,160
 to your failure, is not condemnation.

1067
00:44:20,160 --> 00:44:22,440
 It is compassion.

1068
00:44:22,440 --> 00:44:24,820
 It is compassion.

1069
00:44:24,820 --> 00:44:27,620
 And I wholeheartedly believe,

1070
00:44:27,620 --> 00:44:30,900
 which is why I'm taking the time to get it out of me

1071
00:44:30,900 --> 00:44:32,620
 and give it over to you,

1072
00:44:32,620 --> 00:44:36,820
 that he is asking some of you the same questions tonight.

1073
00:44:36,820 --> 00:44:39,940
 That he's looking at you and he's asking, "Where are you?

1074
00:44:39,940 --> 00:44:40,780
 "Where are you?

1075
00:44:40,780 --> 00:44:42,920
 "You're not where you're supposed to be.

1076
00:44:42,920 --> 00:44:44,000
 "We're supposed to walk.

1077
00:44:44,000 --> 00:44:45,740
 "We're supposed to be with one another.

1078
00:44:45,740 --> 00:44:47,020
 "We're supposed to be in relationship.

1079
00:44:47,020 --> 00:44:47,860
 "Where are you?

1080
00:44:47,860 --> 00:44:49,760
 "You're not where you're supposed to be.

1081
00:44:49,760 --> 00:44:52,780
 "But who told you that?

1082
00:44:52,780 --> 00:44:54,320
 "Why are you listening to those lies?

1083
00:44:54,320 --> 00:44:55,740
 "I didn't tell you that.

1084
00:44:55,740 --> 00:44:56,700
 "I've told you what's true.

1085
00:44:56,700 --> 00:44:58,640
 "I've declared to you that you're mine.

1086
00:44:58,640 --> 00:44:59,480
 "You're my son.

1087
00:44:59,480 --> 00:45:00,320
 "You're my daughter.

1088
00:45:00,320 --> 00:45:01,160
 "You're safe.

1089
00:45:01,160 --> 00:45:01,980
 "You're secure.

1090
00:45:01,980 --> 00:45:03,940
 "You're forever in Christ Jesus by way of the Spirit

1091
00:45:03,940 --> 00:45:04,880
 "into eternal life.

1092
00:45:04,880 --> 00:45:05,980
 "I don't want you just now.

1093
00:45:05,980 --> 00:45:08,140
 "I want you always."

1094
00:45:08,140 --> 00:45:09,740
 He's asking, "What have you done?

1095
00:45:09,740 --> 00:45:12,420
 "What have you done that I cannot clean,

1096
00:45:12,420 --> 00:45:16,140
 "that I cannot fix, that I cannot solve?"

1097
00:45:16,140 --> 00:45:18,580
 He's asking you tonight, "Where are you?

1098
00:45:18,580 --> 00:45:19,640
 "Who told you?

1099
00:45:19,640 --> 00:45:20,860
 "What have you done?"

1100
00:45:20,860 --> 00:45:27,240
 Because I, I can be right when you have been wrong.

1101
00:45:27,240 --> 00:45:30,240
 You may not take responsibility,

1102
00:45:30,240 --> 00:45:32,180
 but I can take responsibility for you.

1103
00:45:32,180 --> 00:45:34,740
 Last story.

1104
00:45:34,740 --> 00:45:40,700
 Just last week, as I'm sure many of you did,

1105
00:45:40,700 --> 00:45:44,060
 and so too did people from all over the globe,

1106
00:45:44,060 --> 00:45:48,620
 I sat down to watch the opening ceremony of the Olympics.

1107
00:45:48,620 --> 00:45:51,260
 And the event was amazing.

1108
00:45:51,260 --> 00:45:53,060
 And towards the end of the time,

1109
00:45:53,060 --> 00:45:55,180
 they do what is ceremonially true

1110
00:45:55,180 --> 00:45:58,000
 of every opening ceremony at the Olympics.

1111
00:45:58,000 --> 00:46:00,300
 They bring in the Olympic torch.

1112
00:46:00,300 --> 00:46:03,140
 Now, I don't know if you know this about the Olympic torch,

1113
00:46:03,140 --> 00:46:06,380
 but the Olympic torch is riddled with symbolism.

1114
00:46:06,380 --> 00:46:07,940
 It is so very significant

1115
00:46:07,940 --> 00:46:12,180
 because that torch is not lit by just any regular old flame.

1116
00:46:12,180 --> 00:46:14,580
 No one just struck a match or pulled out the flamethrower

1117
00:46:14,580 --> 00:46:16,500
 and decided to light the Olympic torch.

1118
00:46:16,500 --> 00:46:18,500
 Instead, it is lit with a different fire.

1119
00:46:18,500 --> 00:46:20,540
 It is lit with a fire from another world.

1120
00:46:20,540 --> 00:46:24,480
 It is lit with the fire from the sun.

1121
00:46:25,940 --> 00:46:30,940
 And that fire is carried from Olympia, Greece,

1122
00:46:30,940 --> 00:46:34,500
 every single games.

1123
00:46:34,500 --> 00:46:38,660
 And it travels miles, thousands of miles

1124
00:46:38,660 --> 00:46:40,660
 to reach its ultimate destination.

1125
00:46:40,660 --> 00:46:46,060
 And so as I saw them bringing the torch in,

1126
00:46:46,060 --> 00:46:47,020
 I was thinking about this moment

1127
00:46:47,020 --> 00:46:48,460
 that I was gonna have with you.

1128
00:46:48,460 --> 00:46:51,100
 And I couldn't help but wonder

1129
00:46:51,100 --> 00:46:54,600
 what happens if something goes wrong?

1130
00:46:56,460 --> 00:46:58,260
 It travels that far.

1131
00:46:58,260 --> 00:46:59,860
 Surely, it's been extinguished.

1132
00:46:59,860 --> 00:47:01,220
 Surely, it's been quenched.

1133
00:47:01,220 --> 00:47:03,180
 Surely, it's burned out at some point.

1134
00:47:03,180 --> 00:47:05,620
 What happens in that event?

1135
00:47:05,620 --> 00:47:09,420
 You wanna know what happens?

1136
00:47:09,420 --> 00:47:13,460
 There is a second flame.

1137
00:47:13,460 --> 00:47:20,140
 There is a substitute that stands in the gap

1138
00:47:20,140 --> 00:47:25,720
 that burns where the first failed to burn brightest.

1139
00:47:26,900 --> 00:47:30,980
 Friends, we have a second flame.

1140
00:47:30,980 --> 00:47:34,700
 We have the second Adam.

1141
00:47:34,700 --> 00:47:39,260
 We have gone wrong, but he has stood in the gap.

1142
00:47:39,260 --> 00:47:40,780
 He has taken our place.

1143
00:47:40,780 --> 00:47:44,300
 He is from another world, but he has stepped into yours.

1144
00:47:44,300 --> 00:47:47,260
 That you might know him, that you might trust him,

1145
00:47:47,260 --> 00:47:49,980
 that you might believe in him,

1146
00:47:49,980 --> 00:47:51,940
 and you might be saved by him.

1147
00:47:51,940 --> 00:47:56,940
 Do you know this compassionate, not condemning king?

1148
00:47:56,940 --> 00:48:04,300
 If you don't, he's asking,

1149
00:48:04,300 --> 00:48:07,600
 where are you?

1150
00:48:07,600 --> 00:48:10,400
 Because I'm here.

1151
00:48:10,400 --> 00:48:14,380
 Let me pray that you would take the invitation.

1152
00:48:14,380 --> 00:48:16,380
 God, I thank you for tonight.

1153
00:48:16,380 --> 00:48:20,660
 Thank you, God, for just the power of your word,

1154
00:48:20,660 --> 00:48:22,860
 the sufficiency of it.

1155
00:48:22,860 --> 00:48:27,860
 I'm grateful, God, that, Lord, you've produced in me,

1156
00:48:27,860 --> 00:48:32,820
 produced in us just this posture of heart that God says,

1157
00:48:32,820 --> 00:48:34,540
 we're not playing games anymore.

1158
00:48:34,540 --> 00:48:39,540
 The world is filled with distraction and division.

1159
00:48:39,540 --> 00:48:40,940
 This will not be a place like that.

1160
00:48:40,940 --> 00:48:42,020
 We will not be distracted.

1161
00:48:42,020 --> 00:48:42,940
 We will not be divided.

1162
00:48:42,940 --> 00:48:44,980
 God, no, we will be devoted.

1163
00:48:44,980 --> 00:48:46,020
 We will be united.

1164
00:48:46,020 --> 00:48:48,780
 And yet, God, as we claim that,

1165
00:48:48,780 --> 00:48:50,660
 we know there's only one name that unites.

1166
00:48:50,660 --> 00:48:54,740
 There's only one name that saves, and it's yours.

1167
00:48:54,740 --> 00:48:55,680
 It's Jesus.

1168
00:48:55,680 --> 00:48:59,540
 Oh, God, I pray,

1169
00:48:59,540 --> 00:49:03,220
 as we said at the beginning,

1170
00:49:03,220 --> 00:49:06,140
 in an evening that matters,

1171
00:49:06,140 --> 00:49:09,200
 won't you prove it to us?

1172
00:49:09,200 --> 00:49:15,260
 Won't you pierce the heart that is within?

1173
00:49:17,100 --> 00:49:19,060
 Pull it out

1174
00:49:19,060 --> 00:49:22,660
 and hold it forever.

1175
00:49:22,660 --> 00:49:26,980
 Christ, we thank you that you lived the life we couldn't,

1176
00:49:26,980 --> 00:49:32,860
 that you died the death we deserve,

1177
00:49:32,860 --> 00:49:34,340
 and you rose forth,

1178
00:49:34,340 --> 00:49:38,900
 and you have made eternal life available to all people

1179
00:49:38,900 --> 00:49:40,900
 if they would place their faith in you.

1180
00:49:40,900 --> 00:49:43,460
 We sing to you now.

1181
00:49:43,460 --> 00:49:45,460
 Oh, God, do we sing.

1182
00:49:45,460 --> 00:49:47,580
 In Christ's name, amen.

